<Layout frontmatter={metadata}>

<p><em>Last Updated: March 2026</em></p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>Launch.Skin ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our website and vanity URL services.</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Names, email addresses, and clinic details voluntarily provided via our setup and contact forms.</li>
    <li><strong>Public Business Data:</strong> To operate the Service, we process your public Instagram handle data and public business details to populate your boutique website.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Data:</strong> Handled via third-party processors (PayPal). We do not store financial info or credit card numbers on our servers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Governing Law</h2>
<p>This Privacy Policy and our privacy practices are governed by the laws of <strong>the State of Delaware, United States</strong>, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any legal actions related to this Policy shall be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in Delaware.</p>

<h2>4. Disclosure of Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell your personal data. We only share info with third-party vendors necessary for hosting, domain routing, and payment processing, or if required by legal obligation.</p>

<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
<p>We implement administrative and technical security measures to protect your personal information. While we take reasonable steps to secure the data you provide, no security measure is perfect or impenetrable.</p>

<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You have the right to request access to the data we hold about you or request its deletion. To exercise these rights or to disconnect your vanity URL synchronization, please contact us directly.</p>

<h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through our <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a>.</p>

